spanishExample: ¿Puedes sentir esto en mi mano derecha?
englishTranslation: Can you feel this on my right hand?

spanishExample: ¿Sientes que te quieres sentar?
englishTranslation: Do you feel like you want to sit down?

spanishExample: El camino correcto es el de la izquierda.
englishTranslation: The right path is the one on the left.

spanishExample: En un momento futuro puedes ir derecho a casa.
englishTranslation: At a future moment you can go straight home.

spanishExample: Está sentado a la izquierda, pero el lado correcto es la derecha.
englishTranslation: He is seated to the left, but the correct side is the right.

spanishExample: Lo siento, no quiero que te sientas triste.
englishTranslation: I’m sorry, I don’t want you to feel sad.

spanishExample: No he sentido lo que estás sintiendo.
englishTranslation: I haven’t felt what you’re feeling.

spanishExample: No me hace falta nada.
englishTranslation: I’m not in need of anything.

spanishExample: No me quiero sentar en el último auto.
englishTranslation: I don’t want to sit down in the last car.

spanishExample: No quiere que me sienta así.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t want me to feel like this.

spanishExample: No sentía que el último era real.
englishTranslation: I wasn’t feeling like the last one(m) was real.

spanishExample: Nunca te sientas a la izquierda.
englishTranslation: You never sit down to the left.

spanishExample: Por favor, siéntese, sé que tiene sueño.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Please, sit down, I know you are sleepy.

spanishExample: Por favor, siéntese, tiene once personas adelante de usted.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Please, sit down; you have eleven people in front of you.

spanishExample: Se ha sentado en la cama, porque tuvo un sueño secreto.
englishTranslation: He has sat on the bed, because he had a secret dream.

spanishExample: Sentí que quince no eran suficientes.
englishTranslation: I felt like fifteen weren’t enough.

spanishExample: Sentía que la falta general de comida era mala.
englishTranslation: She was feeling like the general lack of food was bad.

spanishExample: Sentimos el amor de nuestra familia.
englishTranslation: We felt the love of our family.

spanishExample: Sentimos que deberías sentarte.
englishTranslation: We feel like you should sit down.

spanishExample: Siempre se sienta a la izquierda.
englishTranslation: She always sits down to the left.

spanishExample: Siempre sientan a sus hijos a la derecha.
englishTranslation: They always seat their children on the right.

spanishExample: Sienta a su hijo en el auto.
englishTranslation: He seats his son in the car.

spanishExample: Siente que la idea general no es real.
englishTranslation: He feels like the general idea is not real.

spanishExample: Sienten que el lado derecho es peor ahora.
englishTranslation: They feel like the right side is worse now.

spanishExample: Sientes que necesitas trece, pero doce son suficientes.
englishTranslation: You feel like you need thirteen, but twelve is enough.

spanishExample: Siento que tengo una maldición.
englishTranslation: I feel like I have a curse.

spanishExample: Sintió que la orden no era justa.
englishTranslation: He felt like the order wasn’t fair.

spanishExample: Te sentiste triste ayer porque tu futura familia estaba triste.
englishTranslation: You felt sad yesterday because your future family was sad.

spanishExample: Tengo catorce autos secretos.
englishTranslation: I have fourteen secret cars.

spanishExample: Tienes que ir derecho a ese lugar y sentarte.
englishTranslation: You have to go directly to that place and sit down.
